page.title: 11People - general
page.content: The people of this area fall in to two general categories. Thefamilies who have lived here for many years some working on the land others retired, and those who work outside the area but have chosen country life to that of the suburbs of Leeds. The inhabitants like living in this area it is quiet, apart from aircraft noise from the R.A.F. which is tolerated but is often a topic of conversation especially after a period of night flying. No one interviewed wished to live in a town, but agreed it is a quiet way of life which at times becomes rather boring.
